<paragraph blockId="79.[151,1437,656,2015]" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,439,1952,1979]" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">Sexual dimorphism.</emphasis>
Males can usually be recognized by their smaller size, slender appearance, more rounded humeri, legs stronger with a more noticeable apical mucro, and ventrites 1 and 2 slightly hollowed.
</paragraph>
