<subSubSection pageId="83" pageNumber="84" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="83.[151,1437,152,539]" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,188,215]" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">Distribution.</emphasis>
See Figs. 221, 221a. Sicilian endemic. Known from San Fratello, Passo dei Tre locality in Nebrodi Mountains, at 900–1000 meters of elevation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="83" pageNumber="84" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="83.[151,1437,152,539]" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,261,287]" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">Etymology.</emphasis>
This species is named after our friend and colleague Petrioli (Andrea), specialist in epigean-endogean-hypogean (
<bibRefCitation author="Giachino, P. M. &amp; Vailati, S." box="[337,622,297,323]" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" pagination="1 - 132" refId="ref92151" refString="Giachino, P. M. &amp; Vailati, S. (2010) The subterranean enviroments. Hypogean life, concepts and collecting techniques. WBA Handbooks, 3, 1 - 132." type="journal article" year="2010">Giachino &amp; Vailati, 2010</bibRefCitation>
) beetles, in appreciation and gratitude of his cooperation in our study on 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lacordaire" authorityYear="1863" box="[151,257,333,359]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Peritelini">Peritelini</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="83" pageNumber="84" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="83.[151,1437,152,539]" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,488,369,395]" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">Ecology and Phenology.</emphasis>
